\par }\pard \ltrpar\qj \fi-461\li461\ri0\sa240\widctlpar\wrapdefault\aspalpha\aspnum\faauto\adjustright\rin0\lin461\itap0\pararsid6443588 {\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4231\charrsid3892558 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6443588 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4231\charrsid3892558 You told Miss Sloane that you were born in Dulwich, was that right?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7219173 CW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4231\charrsid3892558 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6443588 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4231\charrsid3892558 And you stayed there about 7 years.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7219173 CW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4231\charrsid3892558 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6443588 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4231\charrsid3892558 After that you moved to Thornton Heath.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7219173 CW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4231\charrsid3892558 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6443588 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4231\charrsid3892558 I wonder if you could tell me why you moved? Was it because of your father's health?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7219173 CW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4231\charrsid3892558 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6443588 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4231\charrsid3892558 Did you make any other moves, as a family, before 1918?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7219173 CW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4231\charrsid3892558 Oh, no. I did, but Mother stayed there with the business, '}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8401400\charrsid3892558 cos}{\rtlch\fcs1 
\af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4231\charrsid3892558  she had to }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8401400\charrsid3892558 \lquote cos}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4231\charrsid3892558  it was her means of livelihood.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6443588 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4231\charrsid3892558 So you stayed on there? It was the family home?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7219173 CW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4231\charrsid3892558 Yes. It was a laundry.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6443588 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4231\charrsid3892558 Have you any idea how old your father was when you were born?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7219173 CW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4231\charrsid3892558 Oh, no, I know he was only a young man. He wasn't an old man. He was a young man. He was a compositor at \{ILLEGIBLE\}
 and, you see, it was the leg poisoning caused him to have Pericarditis. That's the little flesh between the wall of the heart and the heart see, it sort of revolves in a cup. Well, it was the \'85 I suppose they call it a membrane \'85
 round it was eaten by the type, because in those days, you see, the compositors used to put the type in their mouth.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6443588 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4231\charrsid3892558 Did he ever have any other work besides being a compositor?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7219173 CW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4231\charrsid3892558 Couldn't do it.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6443588 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4231\charrsid3892558 And before he was a compositor did he have another job?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7219173 CW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4231\charrsid3892558 Oh, no.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6443588 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4231\charrsid3892558 He'd always been a compositor?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7219173 CW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4231\charrsid3892558 He was apprenticed to it, he served a seven years' apprenticeship and he could only w
ork 8 years. His father was overseer of the composing room.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6443588 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4231\charrsid3892558 How sad.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7219173 CW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4231\charrsid3892558 Yes, it was sad. Sad for my mother, and she was our breadwinner.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6443588 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4231\charrsid3892558 And your mother, how was she in comparison to your father in age?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7219173 CW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4231\charrsid3892558 There wasn't much difference in their ages.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6443588 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4231\charrsid3892558 And before she married, you said, to Miss Sloane, she worked at a hand laundry belonging to Mr. Hayes, is that right?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7219173 CW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4231\charrsid3892558 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6443588 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4231\charrsid3892558 Did she ever do any other work before she married?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7219173 CW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4231\charrsid3892558 No, she was always a shirt ironer. 'Cos those days it was, like }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8401400\charrsid3892558 Hope Bros }{
\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4231\charrsid3892558 but they didn't have the factory like they got now. And they used to send their work to be dressed, their shirts, out to Hayes Laundry.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6443588 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4231\charrsid3892558 I see, and that's where she used to work?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7219173 CW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4231\charrsid3892558 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6443588 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4231\charrsid3892558 When your father was a compositor, before his health was affected, did she work then at all?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7219173 CW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4231\charrsid3892558 No. There was no need to. He earned good money.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6443588 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4231\charrsid3892558 In this house in Thornton Health could you tell me how many rooms there were?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7219173 CW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4231\charrsid3892558 There was about 12.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6443588 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4231\charrsid3892558 It was a large house?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7219173 CW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4231\charrsid3892558 Yes, it was a large house.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6443588 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4231\charrsid3892558 Did you have a parlour, you know, a front room, for entertaining?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7219173 CW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4231\charrsid3892558 Oh, yes. You see, the business was done one side of the house, and there was the privacy the other side.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6443588 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4231\charrsid3892558 The front room, or parlour, what sort of days was it used on? Was it used every day?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7219173 CW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4231\charrsid3892558 Oh, no, not every day. It used to be used on a Sunday, and when the holidays were on.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6443588 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4231\charrsid3892558 What sort of holidays do you mean?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7219173 CW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4231\charrsid3892558 The Bank holidays.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6443588 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4231\charrsid3892558 Did anyone else besides you and your brother and father and mother live in that house?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7219173 CW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4231\charrsid3892558 No.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6443588 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4231\charrsid3892558 You didn't have any lodgers or other relatives?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7219173 CW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4231\charrsid3892558 No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6443588 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4231\charrsid3892558 You said your mother had a daily woman come in to help?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7219173 CW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4231\charrsid3892558 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6443588 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4231\charrsid3892558 She didn't live in?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7219173 CW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4231\charrsid3892558 No. They used to come in daily. There used to be a silk washer - she used to get 3/- a day.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6443588 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4231\charrsid3892558 Just for washing the silk?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7219173 CW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4231\charrsid3892558 
Washing the silks by hand in the wooden tubs. Used to be a long trestle and they used to rest on there. There'd be a silk washer, a shirt washer and the general washer. The general washer used to have the \'85 }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid8401400\charrsid3892558 the}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4231\charrsid3892558  washing for about 3 days, the other two days was plain ironing, hand towels and pillow cases and all the tapes on the pillow cases.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6443588 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4231\charrsid3892558 Did they do any domestic work at all?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7219173 CW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4231\charrsid3892558 They couldn't do, they had to do the business.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6443588 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4231\charrsid3892558 Did your mother do all her own cleaning then?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7219173 CW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4231\charrsid3892558 Yes, she did.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6443588 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4231\charrsid3892558 Nobody helped her with the cleaning?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7219173 CW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4231\charrsid3892558 No. You had to do it yourself.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6443588 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4231\charrsid3892558 Did she have a routine for cleaning? Did she do certain rooms on certain days?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7219173 CW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4231\charrsid3892558 Oh, yes, she used to do her chores \'85 you have to if you're in a business. She did the cooking as well.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6443588 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4231\charrsid3892558 She must have been a terrific worker.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7219173 CW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4231\charrsid3892558 She was. And she used to iron, polish and curl between 3 and 400 collars a day. I used to come home of a 
dinnertime from school, I used to sort that lot and shelves, they was all numbered, you had to mark}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3892558  }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8401400\charrsid3892558 \lquote em}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid4231\charrsid3892558  with a marking ink, and I used to sort all that lot before I went back to school and I helped with dinner and wash up before I went back to school.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6443588 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4231\charrsid3892558 Did any of the people who came in daily have their dinner with you? Did you wash up their ...?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7219173 CW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4231\charrsid3892558 No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6443588 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4231\charrsid3892558 They didn't eat with you?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7219173 CW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4231\charrsid3892558 No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6443588 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4231\charrsid3892558 What did they do then, for their dinner?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7219173 CW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4231\charrsid3892558 They had their own, either went out or brought something with them.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6443588 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4231\charrsid3892558 Was your own family washing done with the laundry?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7219173 CW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4231\charrsid3892558 Oh, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6443588 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4231\charrsid3892558 What did your mother do about clothes? Did she make any of the clothes?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7219173 CW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4231\charrsid3892558 Yes, she did.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6443588 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4231\charrsid3892558 Did she ever buy any?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7219173 CW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4231\charrsid3892558 She used to buy some.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6443588 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4231\charrsid3892558 Where did she buy them from?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7219173 CW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4231\charrsid3892558 Sometimes they used to be bought at Jones }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8731693 &}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid4231\charrsid3892558  Higgins?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6443588 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4231\charrsid3892558 What sort of shop is that?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7219173 CW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4231\charrsid3892558 Oh, a beautiful shop. It's gone down now.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6443588 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4231\charrsid3892558 It's an outfitters, is it?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7219173 CW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4231\charrsid3892558 Yes, at the bottom of our Lane. It was two friends and they used t
o be up every night. And it was only rather a little house at first, the doorway's still there, and these two chaps worked and got that going. Beautiful stuff. There's not the stuff there now that it used to be. 'Course, it isn't Jones }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 
\ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8731693 &}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4231\charrsid3892558  Higgins now, they're both dead.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6443588 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4231\charrsid3892558 What about shoes? Where did she get them?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7219173 CW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4231\charrsid3892558 Oh, same place.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6443588 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4231\charrsid3892558 I remember you said that at one stage your father took over the wash-house.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7219173 CW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4231\charrsid3892558 Yes, sometimes he did, if he felt like it. And then he used to \'85 his 'ealth used to go
. He couldn't do it, you see, his heart couldn't work properly.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6443588 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4231\charrsid3892558 Did he do anything else to help in the way \'85? Repairs \'85?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7219173 CW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4231\charrsid3892558 No, he didn't, that's what we used to go on about. We've gone on about it as we've got older, he had that education and it w
as wasted. He could've done something with it, but he didn't do it.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6443588 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4231\charrsid3892558 Was that because of his health, do you think?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7219173 CW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4231\charrsid3892558 That's what he used to make out, but other people do it.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6443588 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4231\charrsid3892558 He didn't do anything like repairs or improvements, decorating?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7219173 CW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4231\charrsid3892558 No, no, nothing.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6443588 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4231\charrsid3892558 No cooking or housework?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7219173 CW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4231\charrsid3892558 No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6443588 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4231\charrsid3892558 What about you and your brother, do you remember him reading to you or telling you stories, that kind of thing?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7219173 CW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4231\charrsid3892558 No, and with him being a violinist. He's dead.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6443588 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4231\charrsid3892558 Your brother?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7219173 CW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4231\charrsid3892558 Yes. He went to {\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname place}}{\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname country-region}}America{\*\xmlclose}{\*\xmlclose}
, and all. My mother paid for all that, had a tutor at home.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6443588 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4231\charrsid3892558 Did you learn music, too?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7219173 CW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4231\charrsid3892558 Well, not \'85 I wasn't so gifted, you see. And I used to do a bit of singing, but I didn't get hold of the music like he did. He was gifted.

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6443588 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4231\charrsid3892558 Did your mother play, herself?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7219173 CW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4231\charrsid3892558 No. She used to sing.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6443588 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4231\charrsid3892558 And your father?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7219173 CW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4231\charrsid3892558 Oh, there was no music in him! Like a broken-down organ. (laughter)
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6443588 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4231\charrsid3892558 So you didn't have musical evenings at home, or anything like that?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7219173 CW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4231\charrsid3892558 Only when he was playing. We never had a piano.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6443588 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4231\charrsid3892558 Would he play his violin unaccompanied, then?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7219173 CW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4231\charrsid3892558 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6443588 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4231\charrsid3892558 Did you help your brother in any way, do things for him, or was he too close to you in age to sort of look after him?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7219173 CW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4231\charrsid3892558 No, I didn't have to look after him. Mother used to look after him. He always did have bad health. He wasn't very strong.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6443588 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4231\charrsid3892558 In your schooldays, were you expected to get to bed by a certain time? To be indoors by a certain time?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7219173 CW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4231\charrsid3892558 Yes. We were allowed to go out to play.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6443588 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4231\charrsid3892558 Where did you play?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7219173 CW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4231\charrsid3892558 Well, there used to be a lovely field opposite, Grange Wood. 'Course, we used to go over there with our skipping ropes, and that.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6443588 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4231\charrsid3892558 But then did you have to be in by a certain time?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7219173 CW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4231\charrsid3892558 Oh, yes, we had to be in by a certain time.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6443588 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4231\charrsid3892558 What sort of time was that?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7219173 CW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4231\charrsid3892558 Sometimes I used to have to be called in to go and get some beer for the women.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6443588 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4231\charrsid3892558 What time would that be?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7219173 CW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4231\charrsid3892558 'Cos Mother used to have it in, in the cask, see, and 'course, when it run out I used to have to go o
ver with the cans (laughter). They were the days!. And that used to be twice a day, morning and afternoon \'85 evening.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6443588 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4231\charrsid3892558 To get the beer?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7219173 CW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4231\charrsid3892558 Yes. See, they used to work 'till 8 - 9 o'clock.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6443588 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4231\charrsid3892558 Did you mix much with the women, and talk to them?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7219173 CW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4231\charrsid3892558 Oh, no, she wouldn't have it!
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6443588 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4231\charrsid3892558 Did she like to keep the business separate from the family?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7219173 CW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4231\charrsid3892558 Yes, she did.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6443588 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4231\charrsid3892558 I think you said you had your own bedroom to yourself?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7219173 CW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4231\charrsid3892558 Yes, I did.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6443588 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4231\charrsid3892558 Did you put yourself to bed when you were a little girl, or did your mother put you to bed?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7219173 CW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4231\charrsid3892558 
When we were little Mother used to do it, but of course, as we got older we were able to do it. Mind you, I used to keep me own bedroom clean, and me brother's.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6443588 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4231\charrsid3892558 Did you do that on a set day of the week?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7219173 CW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4231\charrsid3892558 Oh, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6443588 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4231\charrsid3892558 What day would that be that you'd have done it?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7219173 CW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4231\charrsid3892558 It'd be a Saturday, or a Monday.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6443588 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4231\charrsid3892558 You worked very hard, didn't you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7219173 CW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4231\charrsid3892558 Yes, I did. I had my}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8401400\charrsid3892558  wack}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid4231\charrsid3892558  of work to do. Used to have to clean the shoes to go to school with every morning.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6443588 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4231\charrsid3892558 Your brother's, too?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7219173 CW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4231\charrsid3892558 
Yes, his as well as mine. And peel the vegetables ready for dinner. Used to peel the potatoes and the Brussels sprouts, and all. I used to detest the beans, cutting them up.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6443588 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4231\charrsid3892558 What about your brother, did he have housework chores?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7219173 CW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4231\charrsid3892558 
No, he never had any household jobs, he was too delicate. The boys used to have a better time than the girls. Yes, they did. Other than that, you couldn't very well give him anything to do 'cos he was put to the violin at 10 years old.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6443588 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4231\charrsid3892558 Did your father clean his own shoes, or did you have to do his, too?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7219173 CW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4231\charrsid3892558 No, he used to do his own.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6443588 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4231\charrsid3892558 Did you have a bathroom, because I know they were rare in those days?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7219173 CW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4231\charrsid3892558 No, we didn't, no, we had what they called a slip bath. That was one that 
had higher backs and low bottom. We used to have our baths in what we called the Stove Room, that was a big terrace stove that they used to hot the irons on. 'Course, that was always nice and warm. That used to be kept on when we were having our baths. We
 didn't have baths every day like they do now.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6443588 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4231\charrsid3892558 How often did you have them?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7219173 CW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4231\charrsid3892558 Once a week.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6443588 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4231\charrsid3892558 Always on the same day?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7219173 CW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4231\charrsid3892558 Oh, yes, every Saturday night, 'cos we had to go to Mass Sunday morning.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6443588 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4231\charrsid3892558 Oh, yes, of course, you said you were Catholics, weren't you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7219173 CW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4231\charrsid3892558 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6443588 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4231\charrsid3892558 People tell me that in those days they had just one set of clean clothes every week, was your family like that?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7219173 CW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4231\charrsid3892558 Yes, that's right.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6443588 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4231\charrsid3892558 And what day would that be, that you had the clean clothes?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7219173 CW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4231\charrsid3892558 Well, the day we had baths. You mustn't put clean clothes on a dirty body.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6443588 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4231\charrsid3892558 I wanted to ask you something about mealtimes in those days. I think you told Miss Sloane that you used to have your meals in the kitchen.

\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7219173 CW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4231\charrsid3892558 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6443588 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4231\charrsid3892558 Were there any occasions when you ate in another room? Or was it always in the kitchen?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7219173 CW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4231\charrsid3892558 Always in the kitchen. We wouldn't have it in the best room, all the crumbs on the floor.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6443588 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4231\charrsid3892558 Did you have breakfast?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7219173 CW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4231\charrsid3892558 Yes, I should think we did!
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6443588 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4231\charrsid3892558 Did you all have it together?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7219173 CW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4231\charrsid3892558 Well, Mum used to be up late, but Father used to do that job, so we always had coarse oatmeal.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6443588 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4231\charrsid3892558 Did he cook that?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7219173 CW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4231\charrsid3892558 Yes, that used to be cooked. And then we'd have either a boiled egg, or egg and bacon. We always had two \'85
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6443588 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4231\charrsid3892558 Two courses?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7219173 CW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4231\charrsid3892558 Yes, two courses with a meal.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6443588 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4231\charrsid3892558 Anything in the way of bread, or anything like that?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7219173 CW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4231\charrsid3892558 Oh, yes, with our bacon, and that. 'Course, it was nice, those days. We used to like it.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6443588 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4231\charrsid3892558 I think you said you weren't allowed butter on toast?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7219173 CW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4231\charrsid3892558 Marge.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6443588 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4231\charrsid3892558 Just Margarine?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7219173 CW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4231\charrsid3892558 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6443588 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4231\charrsid3892558 Was that true of bread, too?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7219173 CW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4231\charrsid3892558 Oh, no, we had butter, then.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6443588 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4231\charrsid3892558 Would you have butter at breakfast time, then, or would you have toast and margarine?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7219173 CW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4231\charrsid3892558 Oh, no. Had butter if you wanted it.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6443588 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4231\charrsid3892558 Did you say your father did breakfast?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7219173 CW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4231\charrsid3892558 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6443588 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4231\charrsid3892558 So did he cook the oatmeal, then?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7219173 CW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4231\charrsid3892558 Yes, he used to cook that.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6443588 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4231\charrsid3892558 And did he cook the eggs and bacon, too?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7219173 CW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4231\charrsid3892558 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6443588 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4231\charrsid3892558 Did your mother stop in bed then?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7219173 CW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4231\charrsid3892558 She used to get up later on.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6443588 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4231\charrsid3892558 Did you have anything to drink?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7219173 CW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4231\charrsid3892558 
Yes, coffee, and we used to grind it, the coffee berries, and the coffee grinder was one of those that used to screw on to the dresser, the shelf of the dresser. Then we used to add the coffee berries. Used to be nice}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid2713424\charrsid3892558 .}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4231\charrsid3892558 . I used to like the coffee.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6443588 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4231\charrsid3892558 Did you ever have milk to drink? I mean a glass of milk, in those days?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7219173 CW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4231\charrsid3892558 Not so much as they do now, you see, the food was better, 'cos it was better food those days.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6443588 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4231\charrsid3892558 And what about dinner? I think you said on Wednesdays and Fridays you'd have fish.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7219173 CW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4231\charrsid3892558 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6443588 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4231\charrsid3892558 Did you all have your dinner together?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7219173 CW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4231\charrsid3892558 Oh, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6443588 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4231\charrsid3892558 The four of you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7219173 CW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4231\charrsid3892558 Yes, rather. It was to see to our manners. Never left on our own at mealtime.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6443588 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4231\charrsid3892558 Did you have a pudding at dinner?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7219173 CW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4231\charrsid3892558 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6443588 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4231\charrsid3892558 Did you have one every day, or only sometimes?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7219173 CW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4231\charrsid3892558 Yes, every day.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6443588 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4231\charrsid3892558 What sort of pudding would it have been?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7219173 CW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4231\charrsid3892558 Sometimes it'd be a plain pudding with syrup, or else especially this time of year we always had suet puddings. Not like they do now, just 
whip it up and no fat in it at all, it was always suet. Sometimes it'd be beef suet, or mutton.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6443588 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4231\charrsid3892558 Did you have fresh fruit ever?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7219173 CW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4231\charrsid3892558 Oh, yes, we used to have it. We had two pear trees in the garden.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6443588 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4231\charrsid3892558 At what meal would you have the fruit, or would that be in between meals?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7219173 CW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4231\charrsid3892558 In between meals.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6443588 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4231\charrsid3892558 Your evening meal, what time of day did you have that?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7219173 CW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4231\charrsid3892558 We had our dinner {\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname time}{\xmlattr\xmlattrns0{\xmlattrname Minute}{\xmlattrvalue 0}}
{\xmlattr\xmlattrns0{\xmlattrname Hour}{\xmlattrvalue 12}}}midday{\*\xmlclose}, and we'd have our tea between 5 and half past. 'Cos we used to come home from school later than they do now.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6443588 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4231\charrsid3892558 And would you have your mother and father there with you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7219173 CW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4231\charrsid3892558 Oh, yes, they'd always be with us.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6443588 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4231\charrsid3892558 What did you have for tea?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7219173 CW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4231\charrsid3892558 Oh, just bread and jam, or bread and marmalade?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6443588 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4231\charrsid3892558 Nothing else?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7219173 CW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4231\charrsid3892558 No. Well, we didn't want it, really. '}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2713424\charrsid3892558 C}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid4231\charrsid3892558 ourse
, it was substantial bread, 'cos we used to have the wholemeal bread. It was all different to what it is now. The food's nothing like what it was then. We used to have dripping, beef dripping or mutton dripping. I used to like the beef dripping, 'cos you 
could stick that in a jar and get all the jelly. 'Cos it used to be put in those stone jars, you don't see those now, that hold about 2 lbs. Of jam. That's what we used to have.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6443588 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4231\charrsid3892558 Did your mother make anything like jam?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7219173 CW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4231\charrsid3892558 Yes, she used to, and marmalade. But of course, she couldn't do a lot. She had the business, and \'85
 We was amazed, we often used to wonder how she did it, sometimes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6443588 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4231\charrsid3892558 The bread came from a baker, did it?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7219173 CW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4231\charrsid3892558 Oh, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6443588 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4231\charrsid3892558 She didn't make bread?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7219173 CW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4231\charrsid3892558 No, she didn't make bread.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6443588 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4231\charrsid3892558 Did she ever make pickles, or bottle fruit?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7219173 CW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4231\charrsid3892558 Very little.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6443588 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4231\charrsid3892558 There wasn't the time, was there?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7219173 CW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4231\charrsid3892558 No. She used to do some.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6443588 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4231\charrsid3892558 You said you had two pear trees in the garden.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7219173 CW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4231\charrsid3892558 Yes.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6443588 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4231\charrsid3892558 Did your family grow any vegetables?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7219173 CW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4231\charrsid3892558 No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6443588 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4231\charrsid3892558 What about livestock, did you ever keep chickens?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7219173 CW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4231\charrsid3892558 Yes, we did. Dogs and chickens.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6443588 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4231\charrsid3892558 What did you keep the chickens for? Just for the family?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7219173 CW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4231\charrsid3892558 Yes, for the eggs, and the \'85 the food \'85 for chicken.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6443588 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4231\charrsid3892558 You ate the chicken?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7219173 CW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4231\charrsid3892558 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6443588 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4231\charrsid3892558 Who would look after the animals, then \'85 the birds?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7219173 CW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4231\charrsid3892558 Mother and Father between 'em.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6443588 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4231\charrsid3892558 Did you have any duties there at all, with the chickens?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7219173 CW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4231\charrsid3892558 No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6443588 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4231\charrsid3892558 Did your mother and father have the same food as you, or did they have different food?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7219173 CW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4231\charrsid3892558 Yes. No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6443588 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4231\charrsid3892558 The same?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7219173 CW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4231\charrsid3892558 Always the same.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6443588 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4231\charrsid3892558 Was Grace ever said at meals?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7219173 CW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4231\charrsid3892558 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6443588 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4231\charrsid3892558 Who used to say it?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7219173 CW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4231\charrsid3892558 And after, Father. Or Mother.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6443588 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4231\charrsid3892558 Was that at all meals, or just on occasions?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7219173 CW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4231\charrsid3892558 Yes. all meals.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6443588 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4231\charrsid3892558 I wanted to ask you a bit about table manners. Were you allowed to talk at meals?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7219173 CW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4231\charrsid3892558 Oh, yes, but not a lot.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6443588 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4231\charrsid3892558 Could you choose what you wanted to eat?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7219173 CW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4231\charrsid3892558 Yes.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6443588 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4231\charrsid3892558 If you didn't want something you weren't compelled to have it?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7219173 CW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4231\charrsid3892558 Well, bread, you see, it all used to be cut up and there'd be two plates, white or brown.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6443588 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4231\charrsid3892558 And you could have which you wanted?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7219173 CW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4231\charrsid3892558 You could have which you wanted.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6443588 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4231\charrsid3892558 And at dinner, for example, if your mother cooked a vegetable you didn't like?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7219173 CW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4231\charrsid3892558 Oh, well, we used to have to eat that, it was food and we had to eat it.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6443588 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4231\charrsid3892558 You had to eat that?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7219173 CW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4231\charrsid3892558 Yes. If you didn't eat it that day you'd have to eat it the next day.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6443588 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4231\charrsid3892558 Really, it would come back, would it?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7219173 CW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4231\charrsid3892558 Oh, yes (laughter)
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6443588 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4231\charrsid3892558 Were there certain vegetables you didn't eat?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7219173 CW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4231\charrsid3892558 Sometimes, parsnips we didn't like, I didn't at first.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6443588 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4231\charrsid3892558 And you'd get that the next day?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7219173 CW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4231\charrsid3892558 Yes, you'd get it the next day.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6443588 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4231\charrsid3892558 And if you accepted some food and left it on your plate uneaten, what would she do then?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7219173 CW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4231\charrsid3892558 Oh, they woul
dn't say anything then, that used to be given over to the animals. You weren't allowed to feed the animals, either, at the food table.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6443588 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4231\charrsid3892558 If they came round begging you couldn't feed them?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7219173 CW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4231\charrsid3892558 No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6443588 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4231\charrsid3892558 If there was something, say the salt was over there where the saucer is, could you ask for it?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7219173 CW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4231\charrsid3892558 Oh, yes, but you had to know how to ask for it.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6443588 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4231\charrsid3892558 Could you ask for a second helping?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7219173 CW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4231\charrsid3892558 Oh, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6443588 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4231\charrsid3892558 Were you expected to sit in a certain way?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7219173 CW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4231\charrsid3892558 You had to sit in your own place.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6443588 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4231\charrsid3892558 Was she particular about how you sat?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7219173 CW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4231\charrsid3892558 
Oh, yes, and the way you used your knife and fork. And you wasn't to make that slapping noise when you was eating. You know how some children do, and some of them they sit like this round the table.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6443588 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4231\charrsid3892558 You weren't allowed to do that?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7219173 CW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4231\charrsid3892558 No fear! Well, it's only right, but you don't see that nowadays.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6443588 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4231\charrsid3892558 Could you bring toys to the table, or a book?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7219173 CW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4231\charrsid3892558 No! No, there was times, you know, you'd make a mess of the book.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6443588 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4231\charrsid3892558 What about starting a meal, did you all start together?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7219173 CW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4231\charrsid3892558 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6443588 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4231\charrsid3892558 When were you allowed to leave the table?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7219173 CW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4231\charrsid3892558 When the parents left.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6443588 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4231\charrsid3892558 You all left together?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7219173 CW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4231\charrsid3892558 Yes. 'Cos, you see, we used to go into the ironing room and annoy the women. 'Course, we weren't allowed to get from th
e table. We used to say, 'please may I leave the table?' 'Well, where do you want to go? What do you want to do? And of course, you couldn't give any answer, see. And start w}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2713424\charrsid3892558 h}{\rtlch\fcs1 
\af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4231\charrsid3892558 impering and you'd get something to }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2713424\charrsid3892558 w}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4231\charrsid3892558 himper for.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6443588 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4231\charrsid3892558 Did you talk much to your mother, was she a person you could talk to?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7219173 CW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4231\charrsid3892558 Oh, yes. Yes, and she used to sing song}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2713424\charrsid3892558 s}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid4231\charrsid3892558  and all, to us. I mean, she was ironing and all she'd sing songs. Oh, she wasn't a miserable woman, it was Father that was miserable. I know I used to feel sorry for 
Mum, I know she never had a holiday for years. Ragged old bits that she used to wear.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6443588 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4231\charrsid3892558 She did?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7219173 CW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4231\charrsid3892558 Yes, she did!
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6443588 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4231\charrsid3892558 Because she was working so hard, you mean?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7219173 CW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4231\charrsid3892558 Yes! And she hadn't got the chance to give it to herself, the kids wanted so much. Look at them early days when they go to school.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6443588 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4231\charrsid3892558 If you were worried about something, would you go to her?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7219173 CW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4231\charrsid3892558 Oh, go to her, we wouldn't go to him.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6443588 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4231\charrsid3892558 You did confide in her, did you, she was that kind of mother?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7219173 CW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4231\charrsid3892558 Yes, yes. He wasn't.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6443588 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4231\charrsid3892558 How did your mother and father expect you to behave towards them? What sort of behaviour did they expect?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7219173 CW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4231\charrsid3892558 Well, you couldn't go beyond it because, you see, they trained you like it and you couldn't go beyond it. You knew how far to go.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6443588 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4231\charrsid3892558 What sort of things did they think important in behaviour? What were their ideas about behaving?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7219173 CW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4231\charrsid3892558 Probably you'd got to behave yourself, you know.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6443588 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4231\charrsid3892558 What sort of people do you think they wanted you to grow up to be? I think some parents had ideas about the 
kind of characters they want their children to have and that kind of thing. Do you think they had ideas about that?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7219173 CW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4231\charrsid3892558 Well, 'course, they wanted us to be up to the mark, 'cos I was sent to Skerry's College, se}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid2713424\charrsid3892558 e, and I couldn't carry it on}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3892558  }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4231\charrsid3892558 account of th
e anaemia. She paid for 2 years' tuition for me. I couldn't do it. Of course, I had to stay home with her 'cos in those days that anaemia used to be very prevalent and, you see, I began to swell. It was like a sort of a dropsy coming on and o' course, I h
a
d to go to the doctor and he told her she'd have to take me away from there, I wasn't having active enough life. And of course I had to go with them in the laundry and I detested that laundry. I used to have to go and fetch the work and take it home. She 
had a little mail cart when we were children, of course, you don't know what they're like.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6443588 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4231\charrsid3892558 I haven't seen them, no.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7219173 CW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4231\charrsid3892558 No, you don't see them now, but there was no chaise or anything in it, you could wheel two children in it, one at the front and on
e at the back, and of course we took this with us when we went over to Thornton Heath and she had this made into what they call a Noah's Ark. She had all the basketwork taken off and it was like a little box put on the top and it was open with a lid. Well
,
 that was for me to go and fetch the washing and take it home. And I used to have a linen bag - she made the linen bag - when the customers paid me I used to put the money in this linen bag and put it in the box. Somebody saw me do it once and they took t
h
e bloomin' lot. I went home crying! And o' course, just a little way up the road there was a lady had a baby and o' course, I used to have to go up there, and o' course, I had to look after the baby while she counted up the washing, so I used to be up the
r
e about an hour and I used to get hell when I got home (laughter). My father used to carry on! And of course I used to say about Mrs. Woodham's baby, so he used to say, 'Mrs. Woodham's baby! Babies are all right when their backsides are powdered like fish
 for frying!' (laughter) And of course, he couldn't come out after me, 'cos, you see, it was a customer and a very good customer and of course, if he'd 'a been funny he'd 'a lost her.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6443588 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4231\charrsid3892558 Why did she keep you so long there?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7219173 CW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4231\charrsid3892558 Well, now, that's what they used to do.. See, I was a little kiddy.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6443588 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4231\charrsid3892558 You mean she'd rather use you to mind her baby while she got on with things?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7219173 CW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4231\charrsid3892558 While she got me the bloomin' linen. And of course, it wasn't only while she counted up, was other work. 'Course, I didn't kn
ow what she was doing, of course, she used to be doing her bedroom and all that upstairs. It wasn't right, though. Oh, I used to get a lot \'85 and then I used to get a lot of money given me.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6443588 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4231\charrsid3892558 Did people give you tips for that kind of thing?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7219173 CW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4231\charrsid3892558 Oh, yes, I used to get a lot of money.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6443588 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4231\charrsid3892558 And you kept that for yourself?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7219173 CW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4231\charrsid3892558 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6443588 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4231\charrsid3892558 Did you tell your father and mother about that?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7219173 CW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4231\charrsid3892558 They knew about it, yes, they knew I had the money.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6443588 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4231\charrsid3892558 What did you spend it on, then?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7219173 CW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4231\charrsid3892558 They used to make me save it, see. You used to get \'85
 it wasn't like Savings Stamps, it was stamps you used to have to stick on something and when it got to so much it used to go in the Post Office. That was how they made us save. But we never had a holiday, never. Neither did Mother. Never.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6443588 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4231\charrsid3892558 Were you often punished?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7219173 CW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4231\charrsid3892558 Not half!
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6443588 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4231\charrsid3892558 You were?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7219173 CW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4231\charrsid3892558 Yes. That's what I didn't like about my father, he was too fond of it. They were, those days.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6443588 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4231\charrsid3892558 Did he punish you more than your mother?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7219173 CW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4231\charrsid3892558 Yes, me mother used to pull him off of us.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6443588 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4231\charrsid3892558 How did he punish you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7219173 CW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4231\charrsid3892558 Well, he used to hit you with his \'85
 one swing and it was nothing to give you a black eye. Oh, he was too spiteful. They were those days. Well his parents used to do the same.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6443588 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4231\charrsid3892558 I remember you said when you swelled up with the anaemia you burst out of your clothes and he used to smack you then
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7219173 CW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4231\charrsid3892558 Yes, he thought I'd been mingling about with some boys.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6443588 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4231\charrsid3892558 What other sort of things would he give you a smack for?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7219173 CW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4231\charrsid3892558 Oh, anything that upset him. If he got neuralgia, or anything, and you happened to make a noise, you'd cop it, then.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6443588 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4231\charrsid3892558 Was your brother the same?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7219173 CW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4231\charrsid3892558 Oh, yes, we were both treated the same. And he was a very delicate boy, he was.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6443588 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4231\charrsid3892558 You said you never had a holiday?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7219173 CW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4231\charrsid3892558 No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6443588 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4231\charrsid3892558 Did you ever go out on a Bank Holiday, say, for a day's outing?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7219173 CW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4231\charrsid3892558 We only used to go \'85 we used to go to the Sunday School treat, or the Band of Hope. That was the only outing to be made.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6443588 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4231\charrsid3892558 Did your mother go with you on those?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7219173 CW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4231\charrsid3892558 Oh, no.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6443588 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4231\charrsid3892558 Just you and your brother?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7219173 CW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4231\charrsid3892558 That's all.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6443588 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4231\charrsid3892558 What about on Christmas Day, did you go out then?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7219173 CW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4231\charrsid3892558 Oh, we always used to have a nice Christmas.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6443588 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4231\charrsid3892558 Did you have any other relatives coming into the home?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7219173 CW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4231\charrsid3892558 No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6443588 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4231\charrsid3892558 Just you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7219173 CW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4231\charrsid3892558 We had relatives, but we never had them in the home.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6443588 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4231\charrsid3892558 Not on any occasions?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7219173 CW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4231\charrsid3892558 No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6443588 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4231\charrsid3892558 Did you go visiting them?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7219173 CW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4231\charrsid3892558 Sometimes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6443588 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4231\charrsid3892558 Did you all go together, the 4 of you, or did you go with one parent?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7219173 CW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4231\charrsid3892558 Oh, we all used to go together.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6443588 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4231\charrsid3892558 Where did the relatives live?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7219173 CW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4231\charrsid3892558 I think some of them lived in Mile End. I don't know, it's so many years ago.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6443588 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4231\charrsid3892558 Did you ever have family prayers in the home?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7219173 CW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4231\charrsid3892558 No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6443588 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4231\charrsid3892558 Do you remember a funeral in the family when you were a child?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7219173 CW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4231\charrsid3892558 No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6443588 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4231\charrsid3892558 Did you have any books, or newspapers in the house?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7219173 CW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4231\charrsid3892558 Yes, I should think we did. 'New Age' and all the Catholic papers; 'Reynolds'. Then they used to go to political meetings.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6443588 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4231\charrsid3892558 Yes, I remember you said they were on the Labour side.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7219173 CW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4231\charrsid3892558 Yes, they were.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6443588 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4231\charrsid3892558 Did she actually work for the labour party?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7219173 CW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4231\charrsid3892558 Well, she didn't have time.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6443588 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4231\charrsid3892558 But she used to find the time for meetings?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7219173 CW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4231\charrsid3892558 Yes, she used to snatch the times for meetings, but she didn't have the time to work at other things.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6443588 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4231\charrsid3892558 Have you any idea why she had the views that she had on politics?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7219173 CW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4231\charrsid3892558 Well, you see, her father was Irish, and he come over from {\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname country-region}}{\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname 
place}}Ireland{\*\xmlclose}{\*\xmlclose} when the potato famine was on. Come over here, and he was an architectural plasterer and he had worked on the {\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname City}}{\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname place}}Westminster{\*\xmlclose}
{\*\xmlclose}, on the clock.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6443588 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4231\charrsid3892558 Do you ever remember them voting, actually going to vote on a General Election before 1918?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7219173 CW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4231\charrsid3892558 Yes. Oh, yes, they used to go voting. Oh, they were proper politicians
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6443588 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4231\charrsid3892558 Did they talk about politics much?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7219173 CW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4231\charrsid3892558 Yes, they did. One had the}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid817253\charrsid3892558 i}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid4231\charrsid3892558 r views and the other one had got his views.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6443588 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4231\charrsid3892558 They weren't both Labour, then?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7219173 CW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4231\charrsid3892558 No, no! His father was a moneyed man, had his own house in Road.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6443588 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4231\charrsid3892558 So what were your father's views, then?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7219173 CW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4231\charrsid3892558 Well, I don't know what his views was, I suppose they must ha
ve been Conservative. Must have been. Well, not so much Conservative in those days, was it. Liberal, or some other thing.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6443588 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4231\charrsid3892558 Did they argue, then, about politics?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7219173 CW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4231\charrsid3892558 Oh, not half! There used to be some arguments.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6443588 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4231\charrsid3892558 Did you join in? Did you have views yourself?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7219173 CW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4231\charrsid3892558 No, I used to listen and if you did join in you were told to mind your own business. (laughter)
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6443588 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4231\charrsid3892558 Do you think they thought that their work would be affected by their political views, at all, the business or anything?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7219173 CW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4231\charrsid3892558 No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6443588 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4231\charrsid3892558 It didn't enter into it?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7219173 CW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4231\charrsid3892558 No, it didn't seem to.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6443588 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4231\charrsid3892558 Because some people used to then, didn't they?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7219173 CW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4231\charrsid3892558 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6443588 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4231\charrsid3892558 Did your father ever go to a club, or pubs?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7219173 CW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4231\charrsid3892558 No. He didn't never drink. Nor smoked.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6443588 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4231\charrsid3892558 And what about your mother, did she go out?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7219173 CW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4231\charrsid3892558 No, she never drank.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6443588 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4231\charrsid3892558 Did your father, before he was ill, take part in sport or go and watch sport at all?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7219173 CW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4231\charrsid3892558 No, no sport.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6443588 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4231\charrsid3892558 Did they not go out, really, at night then?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7219173 CW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4231\charrsid3892558 I don't know 'cos I was too young then to notice all that.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6443588 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4231\charrsid3892558 But when you were older?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7219173 CW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4231\charrsid3892558 No they never went out. They had their business and that was that. That was their life, that was their livelihood.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6443588 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4231\charrsid3892558 Did they ever belong to any savings clubs?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7219173 CW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4231\charrsid3892558 I don't know.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6443588 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4231\charrsid3892558 You said they had friend}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid817253\charrsid3892558 s}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid4231\charrsid3892558 , the customers dropping in.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7219173 CW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4231\charrsid3892558 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6443588 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4231\charrsid3892558 Did they also have friends who weren't customers, who weren't to do with the business?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7219173 CW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4231\charrsid3892558 No, it was always business people, not many neighbours.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6443588 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4231\charrsid3892558 And when the business people came in, did they entertain them at all, give them a cup of tea?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7219173 CW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4231\charrsid3892558 Oh, yes, they used to do that.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6443588 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4231\charrsid3892558 What about having tea together and that kind of thing, did they do that?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7219173 CW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4231\charrsid3892558 Oh, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6443588 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4231\charrsid3892558 They did. I just wondered what the social life was like.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7219173 CW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4231\charrsid3892558 Well, of course, you have to do that sort of thing in business, don't you.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6443588 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4231\charrsid3892558 
I don't know. I don't know much about it, really. I just wondered what the social life was like. And when people called in was it by invitation or was it just casually?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7219173 CW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4231\charrsid3892558 They used to come in sometimes, you know and have a chat. They used to come and see her.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6443588 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4231\charrsid3892558 Did relatives just come in, too?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7219173 CW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4231\charrsid3892558 Sometimes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6443588 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4231\charrsid3892558 Did you ever have any pocket money when you were a child?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7219173 CW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4231\charrsid3892558 Yes, a shilling a week.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6443588 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4231\charrsid3892558 What did you spend it on?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7219173 CW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4231\charrsid3892558 Saved it.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6443588 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4231\charrsid3892558 You were a good girl. What did you save it for?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7219173 CW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4231\charrsid3892558 Well, there was nothing much \'85 I didn't want for anything.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6443588 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4231\charrsid3892558 What about sweets? You didn't want to spend it on sweets?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7219173 CW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4231\charrsid3892558 Well, I could}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid817253\charrsid3892558  }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4231\charrsid3892558 
'a done if I liked, but you see, Mother used to buy all that sort of thing.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6443588 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4231\charrsid3892558 When you were a child who did you play with when you used to play out on that field?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7219173 CW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4231\charrsid3892558 Some of the school children.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6443588 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4231\charrsid3892558 Was she particular about who you played with?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7219173 CW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4231\charrsid3892558 Oh, yes, she was a little bit fussy about it.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6443588 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4231\charrsid3892558 Did she let you get dirty?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7219173 CW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4231\charrsid3892558 Oh, no!
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6443588 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4231\charrsid3892558 You weren't allowed to dirty your clothes?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7219173 CW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4231\charrsid3892558 No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6443588 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4231\charrsid3892558 
I just wanted to ask you about the people round where you were living; were you conscious of the fact that you were in, say, a different class from the people round about you, or were you all the same sort of class, do you think?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7219173 CW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4231\charrsid3892558 
Well, we never had much to do with the people, it was only in the business. You see, when you're in business you've got no time for gossiping with them. I don't gossip with an
y of them here. I've lived here 10 years. This person that's bought this house, she lives next door but one, that's her house as well. I never spoke to her still she come in here, I didn't know who she was.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6443588 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4231\charrsid3892558 But when you were a child did you feel you were better off, say, than children round about you, or worse off?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7219173 CW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4231\charrsid3892558 No, I don't think it ever occurred to us.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6443588 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4231\charrsid3892558 In the country some children were brought up to touch their cap and curtsey, and that kind of thing, were you brought up to anything like that?

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7219173 CW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4231\charrsid3892558 This wasn't the country, it was \'85
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6443588 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4231\charrsid3892558 No, I know, I just wondered if there was anything like that in the town? You weren't brought up like that?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7219173 CW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4231\charrsid3892558 No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6443588 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4231\charrsid3892558 Do you ever remember anyone calling your mother 'madam' or your father 'sir'?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7219173 CW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4231\charrsid3892558 Some of the customers used to when they come.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6443588 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4231\charrsid3892558 And the people that went to the Catholic Church, were they all classes of people?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7219173 CW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4231\charrsid3892558 Oh yes.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6443588 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4231\charrsid3892558 Do you think your mother saw herself as belonging to a particular social class or group, or don't you think she thought in that way?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7219173 CW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4231\charrsid3892558 
I don't know. Well, we never had a lot of that when we were children. At Croydon and Thornton Heath and that, is a select place, it's not like this round here. I don't like it round here, I don't like Camberwell at all
. It isn't like the people in Dulwich, you don't get all that crowd there. You don't see the gossiping like you do round here. You see them round here in bunches, and you know they're talking about you when you're passing, 'cos when you turn round you can
 see 'em looking. I don't like it and I don't like it and I don't have anything to do with them.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6443588 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4231\charrsid3892558 Was your home rented in Thornton Heath?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7219173 CW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4231\charrsid3892558 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6443588 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4231\charrsid3892558 Did you ever come into contact with the landlord? Did you ever meet him?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7219173 CW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4231\charrsid3892558 Oh, yes, he was an old man, lived down Woodstock Road.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6443588 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4231\charrsid3892558 What sort of a landlord was he? How did you feel about him?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7219173 CW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4231\charrsid3892558 Oh, I don't know, that was Mother's and Father's business. Didn't worry me. I'd got the house to live in, that's all that I worried about.

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6443588 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4231\charrsid3892558 Did you ever come into contact with the police at all?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7219173 CW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4231\charrsid3892558 What for?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7219173 CW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4231\charrsid3892558 
Well, seeing them around, you know, and arresting people and that sort of thing in those days. In the village where I live people have told me that they used to be around a lot on Saturday nights, and that kind of thing.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6443588 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4231\charrsid3892558 No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6443588 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4231\charrsid3892558 I just wondered if you remembered the police at all in those days. When you were at the school I believe you said you didn't go to the 
{\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname PlaceName}}{\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname place}}Catholic{\*\xmlclose} {\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname PlaceType}}School{\*\xmlclose}{\*\xmlclose} you went to board school?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7219173 CW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4231\charrsid3892558 Yes, the {\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname PlaceName}}{\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname place}}Catholic{\*\xmlclose} 
{\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname PlaceType}}School{\*\xmlclose}{\*\xmlclose} was too far away.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6443588 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4231\charrsid3892558 How long did it take you to get to the school in Thornton Heath?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7219173 CW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4231\charrsid3892558 Only about 10 minutes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6443588 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4231\charrsid3892558 Did you walk?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7219173 CW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4231\charrsid3892558 Oh, yes, it wasn't far.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6443588 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4231\charrsid3892558 Did you have to have a school uniform?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7219173 CW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4231\charrsid3892558 No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6443588 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4231\charrsid3892558 How did you feel about the teachers at the school?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7219173 CW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4231\charrsid3892558 All right. They never interfered with you.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6443588 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4231\charrsid3892558 Did they punish you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7219173 CW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4231\charrsid3892558 If you needed it. Used to get a cane.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6443588 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4231\charrsid3892558 Girls, too?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7219173 CW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4231\charrsid3892558 Oh, yes. Oh, yes, corporal punishment was very fashionable.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6443588 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4231\charrsid3892558 Were there any gangs or cliques in the school?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7219173 CW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4231\charrsid3892558 What sort of gangs?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6443588 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4231\charrsid3892558 I mean groups of children that went round together and other children were sort of left out of things, you know, as happens in some schools.

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7219173 CW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4231\charrsid3892558 I don't know.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6443588 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4231\charrsid3892558 You don't remember anything like that. Were you quite happy there?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7219173 CW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4231\charrsid3892558 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6443588 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4231\charrsid3892558 Would you have stayed longer at school if you'd had the opportunity, or did you want to leave to go to Skerry's?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7219173 CW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4231\charrsid3892558 We had to leave, you weren't kept at the school after 14.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6443588 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4231\charrsid3892558 Do you remember what the teachers used to think was important in school in those days? Some people say that schools have changed a lot.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7219173 CW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4231\charrsid3892558 
I should think they have! You don't get all the uniform and that like they do now. You didn't have all this going to the colleges and all that like they do. They have altered. Everything's altered.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6443588 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4231\charrsid3892558 Did they emphasise things like manners and punctuality and that kind of thing?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7219173 CW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4231\charrsid3892558 What, in the school?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6443588 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4231\charrsid3892558 When you were there, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7219173 CW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4231\charrsid3892558 Well, you used to get a black mark if you was late. There used to be prizes given, and that. They don't have 'em now.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6443588 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4231\charrsid3892558 What did they give the prizes for?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7219173 CW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4231\charrsid3892558 Anything you done well, or if you got top marks for anything for so long, you used to get a book or something.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6443588 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4231\charrsid3892558 Were they fussy about the way the children spoke, and that kind of thing?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7219173 CW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4231\charrsid3892558 Well yes, they are in the schools, ain't they.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6443588 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4231\charrsid3892558 Before you went to work in the laundry in {\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname City}}{\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname place}}Canterbury{\*\xmlclose}
{\*\xmlclose}, did you have any other paid work? Or did you have any other paid job?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7219173 CW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4231\charrsid3892558 That was only the work I did do.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6443588 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4231\charrsid3892558 You didn't have a part-time job or anything before then?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7219173 CW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4231\charrsid3892558 No, didn't want it. Wasn't part-time jobs about, then.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6443588 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4231\charrsid3892558 Did you have to work on a Saturday when you were in {\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname City}}{\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname place}}Canterbury
{\*\xmlclose}{\*\xmlclose}?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7219173 CW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4231\charrsid3892558 Oh, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6443588 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4231\charrsid3892558 Did you give any money to your mother of the pay that you got?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7219173 CW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4231\charrsid3892558 No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6443588 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4231\charrsid3892558 Because you were living out?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7219173 CW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4231\charrsid3892558 I was living away from home.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6443588 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4231\charrsid3892558 Did you ever belong to a trade union, or anything like that?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7219173 CW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4231\charrsid3892558 No. You don't in the institutions.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6443588 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4231\charrsid3892558 When you first went to work, do you think it changed your attitude to life, or broadened your attitude to life?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7219173 CW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4231\charrsid3892558 Oh, yes it did. You see different people, and all that, and different ideas. You get more involvement, more dances, and all that.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6443588 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4231\charrsid3892558 Did you like laundry work or would you have preferred to do something else if you'd had the chance?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7219173 CW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4231\charrsid3892558 No, I liked it all right.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6443588 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4231\charrsid3892558 Did you like the people you worked with? How did you get on with them?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7219173 CW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4231\charrsid3892558 All right.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6443588 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4231\charrsid3892558 When you were in {\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname City}}{\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname place}}Canterbury{\*\xmlclose}{\*\xmlclose}
 did you continue going to the Catholic Church?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7219173 CW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4231\charrsid3892558 No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6443588 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4231\charrsid3892558 Did you stop going, then?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7219173 CW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4231\charrsid3892558 
Well, I couldn't very well go when I was in the institution. You can't go to Mass and all that, early morning, you've got your living to get. Religion don't keep you.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6443588 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4231\charrsid3892558 Your parents used to come down and see you on their bicycles, didn't they?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7219173 CW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4231\charrsid3892558 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6443588 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4231\charrsid3892558 Did they meet any of the friends you made there?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7219173 CW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4231\charrsid3892558 Yes. Used to come and see me where I was living, and they used to make a fuss of them.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6443588 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4231\charrsid3892558 Make a fuss of your friends, you mean?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7219173 CW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4231\charrsid3892558 No, Mother and Father.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6443588 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4231\charrsid3892558 They welcomed your parents coming to see you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7219173 CW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4231\charrsid3892558 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6443588 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4231\charrsid3892558 At school, did the teachers single out some children for different treatment or did they treat everyone the same?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7219173 CW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4231\charrsid3892558 We was treated all the same.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6443588 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4231\charrsid3892558 Could I ask you when you were born?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7219173 CW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4231\charrsid3892558 1887.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6443588 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4231\charrsid3892558 Whereabouts?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7219173 CW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4231\charrsid3892558 Well I couldn't tell you that exactly, I think it was somewhere in Dulwich.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6443588 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4231\charrsid3892558 Where actually did you spend your childhood?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7219173 CW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4231\charrsid3892558 Seven years in Dulwich, from there we went to Croydon, Thornt
on Heath. My father's health failed, and he was a compositor. Then my mother went into business at Thornton Heath.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6443588 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4231\charrsid3892558 Oh, what sort of business?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7219173 CW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4231\charrsid3892558 Laundry.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6443588 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4231\charrsid3892558 How old were you then?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7219173 CW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4231\charrsid3892558 Seven.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6443588 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4231\charrsid3892558 I see. So your father stayed at home, did he, after that?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7219173 CW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4231\charrsid3892558 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6443588 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4231\charrsid3892558 And how large a laundry was it? How many people had she working for her?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7219173 CW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4231\charrsid3892558 
Oh she had three washers, of course there were different types of washers, there was shirt washers, silk washers and also the, of course hers was more 
of a shirt and collar dressers. She used to take the general work, but she used to charge rather a high price so that she didn't have a lot of it. It was always hand work, and we had a mangle, what they called a box mangle. Yes. We used to work that, I us
ed to work those. And there were four rollers, then you had to, a long mangle and you had to put this up on a, like a lever, and it used to come up on, then you had to be careful you didn't get it down on the bed, the box, of course that was filled}{
\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid817253\charrsid3892558  with}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4231\charrsid3892558  stones and slate, the weight of it.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6443588 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4231\charrsid3892558 She started off her business from scratch then did she?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7219173 CW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4231\charrsid3892558 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6443588 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4231\charrsid3892558 That was very enterprising.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7219173 CW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4231\charrsid3892558 Yes, oh she was a business woman. Oh yes, that was out entire living.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6443588 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4231\charrsid3892558 Had she any experience of this sort of thing?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7219173 CW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4231\charrsid3892558 
Well she used to work for Hayes, that hasn't always been such a big firm as it is now, he used to be called Cocky Hayes and he had a hand laundry, it was all hand work then, but there wasn't the machinery then that there is now.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6443588 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4231\charrsid3892558 Had you a house adjoining?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7219173 CW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4231\charrsid3892558 It was a very big house. Very big it was. And of course we lived there.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6443588 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4231\charrsid3892558 How many rooms would there be?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7219173 CW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4231\charrsid3892558 Oh I forget now, I know we had the living - then there was the ironing room, that was a big place, because we had 
a very long board, on trestles, and there used to four women stand at this board.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6443588 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4231\charrsid3892558 It must have been big.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7219173 CW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4231\charrsid3892558 Yes it was big. You see in those days they had very long tablecloths, see, and they used to iron these, these four women. Then we had a, wha
t they call a Tower stove to heat the irons wi}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid817253\charrsid3892558 th}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4231\charrsid3892558  you see.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6443588 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4231\charrsid3892558 Had you any help in the house at all?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7219173 CW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4231\charrsid3892558 Oh yes, mother used to have the women in. Of course there was the food and all that to get because Father couldn't do a lot.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6443588 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4231\charrsid3892558 She used daily women?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7219173 CW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4231\charrsid3892558 Daily women yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6443588 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4231\charrsid3892558 How many brothers and sisters had you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7219173 CW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4231\charrsid3892558 One brother.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6443588 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4231\charrsid3892558 Was he older?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7219173 CW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4231\charrsid3892558 He was a musician. No he was younger. He was eighteen months younger than me. And he was put to the violin. He was a professional, he is dead 
now.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6443588 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4231\charrsid3892558 Who in fact looked after you as children, as I suppose your mother was rather busy?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7219173 CW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4231\charrsid3892558 She would look after us, yes. We never had anybody to look after us. Oh we had our whack of work to do, I did.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6443588 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4231\charrsid3892558 What sort of things did you do?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7219173 CW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4231\charrsid3892558 W
hen I came home from school, I used to have to lay out the lunch, well then Mother had got all the collars and that sorted, because she used to have a few hundred for them when she had got them all done, I used to have to sort these, when I came home from
 school. Of course they were all marked with cotton, see, and ink, and I used to have to sort them all out for the different customers. And then there used to be shelves to put the shirts on, and they all had to be wrapped up.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6443588 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4231\charrsid3892558 So you had a fair bit on then?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7219173 CW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4231\charrsid3892558 
Oh yes. we didn't have much playtime when I was little. And then I had a little, I don't suppose you remember the mail carts, no you wouldn't. Well when we were children we had a mail cart, that was a child to sit in the front and one at the ba
ck. When she got into the laundry she had this altered and made into a little, like a Noah's {\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname place}}{\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname State}}Ark{\*\xmlclose}{\*\xmlclose}
 see. And it had a lid, and it wasn't very hard to push, but I used to have to take this round to collect the washing from the customers, also take it home.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6443588 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4231\charrsid3892558 How large an area, was it a local sort of a business?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7219173 CW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4231\charrsid3892558 Yes. Yes it was local. She didn't have any horse and van, no.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6443588 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4231\charrsid3892558 What sort of an area was it wound there?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7219173 CW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4231\charrsid3892558 Very nice, very select. Yes. It was after the style of Hampstead, well you have
 heard of Croydon, this was a little way out. Oh I should think it has altered. Yes, that is where we used to live. There for years.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6443588 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4231\charrsid3892558 Had you a garden at this house?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7219173 CW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4231\charrsid3892558 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6443588 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4231\charrsid3892558 How big was it?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7219173 CW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4231\charrsid3892558 Oh lovely because that's where we used to do the drying.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6443588 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4231\charrsid3892558 Oh did you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7219173 CW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4231\charrsid3892558 
Yes, the stuff used to be dried out of doors. Yes. When the weather was nice, and when it was wet, in the winter time, we used to have blinds up over the, it was what we called the stove room, where the stove was, because it
 had pipes. There was a pipe come up from the stove, the ironing stove, and used to go through the wall and across, right up through the flue. And we used to hang the washing up on these lines. Of course it used to be filled up of a night and the things w
ere dry in the morning.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6443588 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4231\charrsid3892558 What would your father do this?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7219173 CW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4231\charrsid3892558 Yes he did that.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6443588 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4231\charrsid3892558 Was he staying at home all the time?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7219173 CW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4231\charrsid3892558 Oh yes. Well Mother used to say he got his education but he never used it.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6443588 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4231\charrsid3892558 Would you see your father much.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7219173 CW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4231\charrsid3892558 Oh he would be home all the day.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6443588 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4231\charrsid3892558 Would he play with you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7219173 CW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4231\charrsid3892558 Sometimes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6443588 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4231\charrsid3892558 Was he the sort of father who -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7219173 CW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4231\charrsid3892558 Oh he wasn't a very generous man. He thought Mother had got the business and she could keep it.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6443588 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4231\charrsid3892558 It obviously made a reasonable sort of living anyway.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7219173 CW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4231\charrsid3892558 Oh yes it did.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6443588 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4231\charrsid3892558 You were nicely off?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7219173 CW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4231\charrsid3892558 Yes, oh yes we were nicely off.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6443588 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4231\charrsid3892558 How old were you when you started work? I mean when you started school?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7219173 CW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4231\charrsid3892558 Well I went to the, um, in Croydon, Thor}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid817253\charrsid3892558 n}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid4231\charrsid3892558 ton Heath Road School, and of course you know you had to leave school at }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid817253\charrsid3892558 14}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4231\charrsid3892558 
 in those days. Well then I went to Skerry's College from there. That was for the Civil Service, see. Mother paid for two years tuition.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6443588 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4231\charrsid3892558 Whereabouts was this?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7219173 CW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4231\charrsid3892558 Skerry's College was at the top of {\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname address}}{\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname Street}}Katharine Street
{\*\xmlclose}{\*\xmlclose} at Croydon. And she paid for two years tuition for me and I couldn't carry it on. It was too much sitting. It didn't suit me. I was always ill.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6443588 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4231\charrsid3892558 What sort of subjects were you doing then?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7219173 CW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4231\charrsid3892558 Well there was cross tots. - do you know what th
ey are. Well there's figures right across the page, and there is about half a dozen columns, and I think there was four or six rows and you had to count those up across, and sometimes you would get mixed up with it! See. Yes, it was hard work. And then th
e
re was manuscript writing I used to have to do. Special pens and all we used to have to have for the Civil Service, see. And oh there was a load of Geography. And it was a thing I hated. History, yes. And we used to have to do map drawing and all. Yes, th
a
t used to be the different areas, course in the Civil Service you had to do all that see. But I couldn't keep it up. Cos they used to, well me blood was, it was kind of anaemia, it was very prevalent in those days. And you see me blood was turning to wate
r
. And of course mother used to make all my clothes, well I was getting stouter and two or three times I burst me clothes here. And Father thought I had been roughing about with some boys and got it torn and I used to get a smack in the ear for it. But I w
asn't, I was ill. Of course the doctor told her, "Well you will have to take her away from there, she'll never be any good with it" so of course I had to stay home with her.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6443588 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4231\charrsid3892558 How did you like your first school?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7219173 CW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4231\charrsid3892558 Oh I didn't dislike it, it wasn't that.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6443588 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4231\charrsid3892558 Were the teachers strict?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7219173 CW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4231\charrsid3892558 
Oh yes they were strict in those days. Often used to have to go to the Governess. If you'd done anything wrong, what they thought was wrong. I never got me scholarships though, they used to get all those type of th
ings at school. But I used to belong to a Band of Hope. And that was very nice. And they used to have nice contests there. One contest was what they called a Spelling Bee. Well there was a lot of children there, and one boy was, though he was at Universit
y, he was older than me, and of course a lot of us went in for this Spelling Bee. Well I got second prize, he got first.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6443588 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4231\charrsid3892558 How old would you have been then?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7219173 CW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4231\charrsid3892558 Oh I suppose I was about }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5973678\charrsid3892558 13}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid4231\charrsid3892558  to }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5973678\charrsid3892558 14}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4231\charrsid3892558 . I used to like that, it was ever so nice.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6443588 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4231\charrsid3892558 Who organized it?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7219173 CW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4231\charrsid3892558 
It was a gentleman who worked in the Civil Service, Mr. Kennedy, he died in the end, oh, he did work hard for that Band of Hope. And we used to have some things, cantatas we used to have, and shows. One cantata was called the "Wild Garland" 
we were all in white and we had singing and all. Oh it was nice. It was really better than school. He had such a nice way with him. We wouldn't dare miss this.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6443588 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4231\charrsid3892558 How often was it?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7219173 CW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4231\charrsid3892558 Once a week. Every Tuesday. Every Tuesday evening. I used to enjoy this. Of course our parents used to come and see us doing things.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6443588 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4231\charrsid3892558 Had you any outings organized by the Band of Hope?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7219173 CW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4231\charrsid3892558 Not a lot. Only about once a year. Not like the children do now.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6443588 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4231\charrsid3892558 Where would you go to?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7219173 CW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4231\charrsid3892558 Oh to the seaside. Probably Margate.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6443588 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4231\charrsid3892558 Was Skerry's very different from your first school?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7219173 CW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4231\charrsid3892558 Oh yes. It was a commercial school. A commercial school
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6443588 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4231\charrsid3892558 So what sort of difference actually -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7219173 CW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4231\charrsid3892558 Well we had men teachers, men teachers. Every other day I used to have to go mo
rning, afternoon and evening, and then next day would be for half a day and we didn't half used to have a load of homework. At that time I think it was Queen {\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname place}}{\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname State}}Victoria
{\*\xmlclose}{\*\xmlclose} died, and we had to write an essay on her. That's one subject we had to do. And then we h
ad to do a lot, of course they had a different style of writing to the schools and we had to do a lot of copy writing. Yes, and copy books, and we used to have to do the writing. There would be a sample at the top and you used to have to write it like tha
t. Of course we had special pens. I forget what pens they were now, I did know a little while ago -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6443588 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4231\charrsid3892558 How large were the classes there?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7219173 CW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4231\charrsid3892558 I think they used to have to be in there at half past }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5973678\charrsid3892558 9}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 
\ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4231\charrsid3892558 , half past }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5973678\charrsid3892558 9}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4231\charrsid3892558  to }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5973678\charrsid3892558 12}{
\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4231\charrsid3892558 , and I used to come home to lunch and then come back it was the blessed fare you know.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6443588 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4231\charrsid3892558 How far away was it?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7219173 CW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4231\charrsid3892558 It was at Croydon and I was living at Thomton Heath.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6443588 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4231\charrsid3892558 Would you walk?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7219173 CW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4231\charrsid3892558 No ride. Oh I couldn't have walked that distance. No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6443588 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4231\charrsid3892558 Did you enjoy Skerry's?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7219173 CW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4231\charrsid3892558 Yes I did, I liked Skerry's. I was sorry I had to leave.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6443588 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4231\charrsid3892558 What sort of children were there, were they from a similar background?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7219173 CW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4231\charrsid3892558 No, it was all paid for. It was like the trades peoples daughters.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6443588 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4231\charrsid3892558 Was it only girls or was it boys as well?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7219173 CW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4231\charrsid3892558 Oh boys as well. There was a publicans daughter there, and then there was a niece or something of Grants, the dra}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 
\ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5973678\charrsid3892558 p}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4231\charrsid3892558 ers at - I suppose she was being educated for the business.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6443588 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4231\charrsid3892558 Had you many friends there? Or were your friends locally from round home?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7219173 CW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4231\charrsid3892558 
No, I didn't have many friends. Well you didn't have time for them. What with the business, always had plenty of work to do at home. We was never allowed in the streets. Never.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6443588 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4231\charrsid3892558 I suppose your mother was rather particular about who you played with?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7219173 CW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4231\charrsid3892558 
Oh yes. And of course we had customers and that and I used to go round like to get the washing and take it home and of course I used to get in their places. Well then I had pillow cases and hand towels and all that to blessed well iron and table napki
ns I had to iron. And then I used to have to pack the baskets. Because you see we had little hampers like for shirts and collars because it was mostly shirts and collars we used to do.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6443588 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4231\charrsid3892558 After you had left Skerry's was this?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7219173 CW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4231\charrsid3892558 Oh yes, I had to stop home with her then.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6443588 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4231\charrsid3892558 Hadn't you any option?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7219173 CW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4231\charrsid3892558 
I didn't care for it. But what could I do? Of course in those days you had to do as your parents told you. Whether you like it or not. But now it is different.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6443588 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4231\charrsid3892558 Were they strict with you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7219173 CW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4231\charrsid3892558 Yes, they were in those days?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6443588 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4231\charrsid3892558 What sort of things? Table manners?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7219173 CW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4231\charrsid3892558 Oh over table manners yes. My brother used to sit next to Mother, I had to sit next to Father.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6443588 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4231\charrsid3892558 Were they strict over staying out at night?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7219173 CW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4231\charrsid3892558 Didn't get a chance. no. Didn't get a chance.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6443588 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4231\charrsid3892558 Had you any sort of social life at all?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7219173 CW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4231\charrsid3892558 Only with the Band of Hope. Then I got fed up with being as I got older. Then I wanted to come out. So I w}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid5973678\charrsid3892558 e}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4231\charrsid3892558 nt into the Institutions. It appealed to me. The one that I went to was at {\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname place}}{\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname City}}Can}{
\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5973678\charrsid3892558 t}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4231\charrsid3892558 erbury{\*\xmlclose}{\*\xmlclose}. We had to live out, see. And -
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6443588 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4231\charrsid3892558 What were you doing?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7219173 CW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5973678\charrsid3892558 Head laundr}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4231\charrsid3892558 es}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5973678\charrsid3892558 s}{
\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4231\charrsid3892558 . I was there 'till the blessed war come on.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6443588 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4231\charrsid3892558 How did you find that job?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7219173 CW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4231\charrsid3892558 It was advertised. And of course you had to go and see these people. She was a Scotch Matron
, she was very nice. And there was a doctor that interviewed you. They wanted to know a lot, they did. I wonder how some of them get in these places now, very nice though. And you see we were allowed lodging money. And it was with one of the staff. That l
ived there, he was not a porter, an attendant in there, he was. And of course he had a room.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6443588 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4231\charrsid3892558 And you lived there? I see.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7219173 CW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4231\charrsid3892558 And we had to have our meals like, over there, at the weekend, of course we didn't work the weekend, not after Saturday after
noon, Sunday we used to be off.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6443588 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4231\charrsid3892558 What sort of hours did you work in the week?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7219173 CW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4231\charrsid3892558 Oh it was about }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5973678\charrsid3892558 8}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4231\charrsid3892558 
 in the morning and it would be about }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5973678\charrsid3892558 5}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4231\charrsid3892558  or }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5973678\charrsid3892558 6}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 
\ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4231\charrsid3892558 . See it was more like a private album. Top of St. Martins Hill.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6443588 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4231\charrsid3892558 How many were there of you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7219173 CW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4231\charrsid3892558 Four. And we used machines, and of course the patients used to come and help you.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6443588 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4231\charrsid3892558 How did you like it there?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7219173 CW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4231\charrsid3892558 Oh I liked it very much. Nice clean place it was.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6443588 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4231\charrsid3892558 Were they nice employers?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7219173 CW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4231\charrsid3892558 Yes. Yes, the nice, the matron used to come round s
ee, she used to come round and see us. Come round about twice a week, she was a Scotch Matron.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6443588 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4231\charrsid3892558 What were your wages when you started working there?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7219173 CW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4231\charrsid3892558 Oh I forget now, I know they weren't bad. Of course we had our living out money and that helped us. And then we used to have nice holidays.

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6443588 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4231\charrsid3892558 Oh, you were fairly nicely off then?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7219173 CW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4231\charrsid3892558 Yes, I was, I was all right then, and of course your people used to come and see you. Mum used to come down of a weekend and that.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6443588 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4231\charrsid3892558 How old were you when you first went there?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7219173 CW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4231\charrsid3892558 Well it was when the, when that blessed war broke out.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6443588 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4231\charrsid3892558 1914?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7219173 CW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4231\charrsid3892558 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6443588 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4231\charrsid3892558 You had stopped at home until then?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7219173 CW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4231\charrsid3892558 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6443588 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4231\charrsid3892558 What did your parents think about you going away from home?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7219173 CW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4231\charrsid3892558 They didn't say much. No, they couldn't could they? I didn't always want to be home there.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6443588 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4231\charrsid3892558 Had your brother left home?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7219173 CW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4231\charrsid3892558 
Well you see he had the violin and of course he cost Mother a lot of money and of course he went, he went to America and all. And when he got over there, of cou
rse there's a lot of picking out there, and when they heard him play, I forgot where it was he was going to and the man said to him "You're a God damned Englishman but I shall have to have you, you can play it!" See.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6443588 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4231\charrsid3892558 So he was a professional?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7219173 CW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4231\charrsid3892558 Yes. Violin. He's dead now.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6443588 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4231\charrsid3892558 Had you any holidays when you were children?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7219173 CW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4231\charrsid3892558 Not much. You couldn't really -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6443588 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4231\charrsid3892558 Not with the business.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7219173 CW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4231\charrsid3892558 No we would have had to close it up. You couldn't do that those days.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6443588 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4231\charrsid3892558 Had you relatives to go to or anything?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7219173 CW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4231\charrsid3892558 Not much.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6443588 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4231\charrsid3892558 Had your parents any outside interests or were they rather -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7219173 CW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4231\charrsid3892558 Always too hard at work. Mother was always at work.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6443588 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4231\charrsid3892558 How about your father then?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7219173 CW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4231\charrsid3892558 Him? Oh he didn't do much.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6443588 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4231\charrsid3892558 He must have had spare time?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7219173 CW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4231\charrsid3892558 Well he used to muck about in the place, you know. In the end he took over the wash house.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6443588 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4231\charrsid3892558 Had you any newspapers or books in the house?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7219173 CW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4231\charrsid3892558 Not those years ago.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6443588 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4231\charrsid3892558 Hadn't your parents a newspaper?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7219173 CW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4231\charrsid3892558 Yes, they used to have newspapers, "Croydon T
imes" and I forget what it is they used to take "The Daily worker" I think it was, they used to take.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6443588 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4231\charrsid3892558 was your father interested in politics?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7219173 CW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4231\charrsid3892558 Oh yes, he was, he was a proper politician.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6443588 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4231\charrsid3892558 Was he?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7219173 CW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4231\charrsid3892558 So was mother.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6443588 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4231\charrsid3892558 That's interesting, what were they?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7219173 CW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4231\charrsid3892558 
More on the labour side. They weren't Conservative. Neither am I. I don't believe in the Conservatives. No I don't!! Some of them go on about the Labour people but I think {\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname place}}{\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname City}}Wilson
{\*\xmlclose}{\*\xmlclose} has done well. I do think so. He never went to any University you know. I never knew that until my grandson told me. You're not compelled to go to any }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5973678\charrsid3892558 u}{
\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4231\charrsid3892558 niversity, {\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname City}}{\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname place}}Wilson{\*\xmlclose}{\*\xmlclose} didn't go and look where he's gone!! I don't think he's done bad at all.

\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6443588 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4231\charrsid3892558 was your father actively interested in politics?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7219173 CW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4231\charrsid3892558 Oh yes, so was Mother.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6443588 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4231\charrsid3892558 what would they do?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7219173 CW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4231\charrsid3892558 They used to go to the political meetings. Oh yes. They used to find time for that.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6443588 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4231\charrsid3892558 I should have thought, actually, having a business would have made them keep their politics quiet.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7219173 CW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4231\charrsid3892558 Oh no. Mother was Irish. Irish descent of course. Well her father was Irish, he come over from {\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname country-region}
}{\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname place}}Ireland{\*\xmlclose}{\*\xmlclose}, her father did, when the potato famine was on. He was an architectural plasterer.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6443588 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4231\charrsid3892558 They were both staunch socialists then?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7219173 CW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4231\charrsid3892558 Oh yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6443588 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4231\charrsid3892558 Would they do anything at election times?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7219173 CW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4231\charrsid3892558 No, they used, no they didn't do, no she had too much time in the business. She didn't go for any holidays for years.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6443588 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4231\charrsid3892558 were you interested in politics when you were young?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7219173 CW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4231\charrsid3892558 No, I used to think it was a nuisance.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6443588 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4231\charrsid3892558 Why?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7219173 CW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4231\charrsid3892558 Oh there used to be arguments about them. It didn't interest me}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5973678\charrsid3892558 .}{\rtlch\fcs1 
\af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4231\charrsid3892558  I had done later years though.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6443588 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4231\charrsid3892558 Did your parents have friends visiting them at all?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7219173 CW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4231\charrsid3892558 Yes, they did do. Well you do with a business don't you, yes. If you have got a business you do have friends or customers come and see you}{
\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5973678\charrsid3892558 , you}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3892558  }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4231\charrsid3892558 know.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6443588 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4231\charrsid3892558 Who did the paper work side of the business?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7219173 CW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4231\charrsid3892558 Father. I had to do some. The wages books and all. It was piece work in those days. The, some of the workers were paid 2/-, 2/6d., 2/9d, 3
/- per day. They used to have beer, no cups of tea, beer. Beer in the morning and beer at night. And it used to come in the casks. 4}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3892558  1/2}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4231\charrsid3892558 
 gallons. Sometimes it used to run out and I used to have to go over to the pub, I used to wish them to the devil, half 
a pint of porter and a penny on the can! Over at the Grange Hotel. One woman would come in, she was a shirt washer, "Governor, can I have my beer now?" before ever she started work! Oh she was a drunken old crab. And then Saturday, they didn't come in Sat
urday so these women used to go out selling flowers, baskets for the flowers.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6443588 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4231\charrsid3892558 Had you shops round about?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7219173 CW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4231\charrsid3892558 Oh yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6443588 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4231\charrsid3892558 Would your mother buy most of her things locally then?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7219173 CW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4231\charrsid3892558 No, she used to get a lot of her stuff from Spiers }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8731693 &}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid4231\charrsid3892558  Ponds (?) they
 used to deliver then you see. So the provisions and that, like butter and bacon, she used to go to Sainsburys. We used to get beautiful butter for 1/- a pound at Sainsburys. It used to be so hard in the winter that you had to put it up under the stove to
 get it warm to spread it. The only time it would be nice on the bread was when you toasted it. And you wasn't allowed butter then you was allowed margarine on your bread for your toast.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6443588 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4231\charrsid3892558 Would your mother have much time actually for making meals?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7219173 CW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4231\charrsid3892558 Oh yes, she used to do our meals. She used to find the time.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6443588 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4231\charrsid3892558 Would you have meat every day or only on Sundays?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7219173 CW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4231\charrsid3892558 Certain days, Wednesdays would be fish, and Fridays. Plaice. Big plaice. Not like the little plaice you get now, big. Lovely plaice.
 Or else we'd have cod with parsley sauce.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6443588 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4231\charrsid3892558 What other sorts of things would you have?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7219173 CW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4231\charrsid3892558 She used to fry it on a Friday, Wednesdays it used to be boiled.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6443588 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4231\charrsid3892558 What other things did you have on Mondays, Tuesdays and Thursdays?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7219173 CW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4231\charrsid3892558 Oh we would have a nice piece of beef. And it would be roasted in front of the fire, see, you'd have to keep turning it round and basting it.

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6443588 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4231\charrsid3892558 On a Sunday would that be?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7219173 CW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4231\charrsid3892558 Any time. Yes. No electricity, all coal fires. Used to burn coke for our ironing stove.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6443588 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4231\charrsid3892558 What sort of a kitchen had you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7219173 CW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4231\charrsid3892558 
Oh a big one, it had two ovens. And it had - boiler and a brass tap, and all that had to be cleaned up. And steel top fenders with "Home Sweet Home". Blessed work. There wouldn't half be some work!
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6443588 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4231\charrsid3892558 Would you have your meals in the kitchen?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7219173 CW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4231\charrsid3892558 
Oh yes. There was always plenty of warmth. My bedroom used to be over the stove room so I was all right! Yes. My brother had a bedroom over the hall, oh it was a big hall, lovely hall it was. We had a hat stand in there, 
and a little hall table. Of course she used to go to Mass, she was Catholic. She used to go to Mass, oh yes. Early morning.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6443588 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4231\charrsid3892558 Every Sunday?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7219173 CW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4231\charrsid3892558 Oh yes, I think sometimes in the week.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6443588 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4231\charrsid3892558 How about your father?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7219173 CW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4231\charrsid3892558 Never went.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6443588 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4231\charrsid3892558 What happened about you children then?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7219173 CW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4231\charrsid3892558 Oh we had to go. Oh yes we had to go as well!! It was too far away though for the {\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname PlaceName}}Catholic
{\*\xmlclose} {\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname PlaceType}}School{\*\xmlclose}, it was about three miles to the {\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname PlaceName}}Catholic{\*\xmlclose} {\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname PlaceType}}School{\*\xmlclose}
, so we had to go to the {\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname place}}{\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname PlaceName}}Board{\*\xmlclose} {\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname PlaceType}}School{\*\xmlclose}{\*\xmlclose}. Yes it was a long way. We used to have to g
o that way to Church though. Well then they built one in Thornton Heath, a Church, and it was nearer.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6443588 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4231\charrsid3892558 How old would you be then?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7219173 CW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4231\charrsid3892558 Oh school age.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6443588 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4231\charrsid3892558 You went every Sunday then?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7219173 CW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4231\charrsid3892558 Oh yes, wet or fine! Whether we wanted to go or not you had to go.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6443588 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4231\charrsid3892558 They hadn't any sort of Sunday School had they?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7219173 CW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4231\charrsid3892558 
The Catholics don't. The Catholics don't. (I think our old Pope's daft over this Pill business - what does he know? He is not a married man! I think the Catholics do have too many children, look at Mrs. Kennedy. I think it is too many.)
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6443588 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4231\charrsid3892558 It's all right if you can afford it isn't it?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7219173 CW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4231\charrsid3892558 
Yes. And if you've got somebody else to help you bring them up. You can't bring them all up on your own like that. He doesn't know what he is talking about.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6443588 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4231\charrsid3892558 Were there a lot of Catholics round you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7219173 CW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4231\charrsid3892558 Yes, there were.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6443588 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4231\charrsid3892558 After you started working, what would you spend your evenings off doing?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7219173 CW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4231\charrsid3892558 Oh we used to go to Church, and sometimes we'd go, if the weather was kind we'd go for walks. We used to go to dances. 
{\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname place}}Lot{\*\xmlclose} of dances in the town.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6443588 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4231\charrsid3892558 Did you make friends in {\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname City}}{\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname place}}Canterbury{\*\xmlclose}{\*\xmlclose} then?

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7219173 CW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4231\charrsid3892558 Oh yes. You see it was a military town. And they used to do, a lot of practise the}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid2690719\charrsid3892558 re on the, just opposite our As}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4231\charrsid3892558 ylum, there used to be the horse riding and all there.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6443588 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4231\charrsid3892558 So what happened after the War broke out, you stayed on there did you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7219173 CW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4231\charrsid3892558 
No, you couldn't stay. It was all in darkness. Yes. And there was little boys had to come down there and be billeted, little boys they were. And they was called o
ut in the middle of the night, you had to give up your front room because we were living out. Well the people that had the houses, they had to give up their front room for these boys to be billeted there. They were only training, and they would be called 
o
ut in the middle of the night. Never had their clothes off? And it was all in pitch darkness. And it began to get too dangerous because it was right, not far from the coast, of course I had to leave there, too nervous. Too nervous. Well then I go, there w
as a 9}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \super\insrsid4231\charrsid3892558 th}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4231\charrsid3892558  Lancer Station there and I got, it was only through the dancing that I picked up with a 9}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\super\insrsid4231\charrsid3892558 th}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4231\charrsid3892558  Lancer, yes and the poor devil got killed.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6443588 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4231\charrsid3892558 Had you known him long?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7219173 CW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4231\charrsid3892558 Yes, I'd known him for two years, we was engaged an all. In the end he got kil
led or we should have been married. He was coming cut of the blooming army too, there was a job an all down there for him in the prison, he was going to be a prison warder. Got killed. And he wasn't fighting. The Regiment was resting. Never forget that bl
ooming letter come, I never took it in. Right on the corner of the envelope "Casualty No. so and so! My father took the letter in. As his voice faltered he says to Mother "It is from {\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname City}}{\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname 
place}}Canterbury{\*\xmlclose}{\*\xmlclose}"2 My mother did cry, she liked him, he was a nice fellow, he was a Yorkshireman. He was nice. He had no father.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6443588 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4231\charrsid3892558 Yes, so he met your parents and everything seemed -
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7219173 CW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4231\charrsid3892558 
Yes, my mum liked him. You couldn't help liking him. Nice and dark he was. Yes, it was - because he was coming out that very year. It was luck. It would have been a nice job down there too. They had a nice house and all.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6443588 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4231\charrsid3892558 Were you parents strict over the boys you went around with?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7219173 CW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4231\charrsid3892558 They didn't used to say much. Oh you couldn't take anybody home - no fear!
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6443588 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4231\charrsid3892558 But you were able to go out by yourself then?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7219173 CW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4231\charrsid3892558 Oh yes. We used to have a cycle. Oh yes, I used to have a cycle. I took that down to {\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname place}}
{\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname City}}Canterbury{\*\xmlclose}{\*\xmlclose} with me. And of course we used to go for rides on our bicycles, Mum used to come down on a bicycle, yes, so did Father. Oh yes they used to come down.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6443588 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4231\charrsid3892558 It sounds very pleasant in Canterbury.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7219173 CW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4231\charrsid3892558 
Oh it is lovely down there, I used to like it down there. Yes, I did like it. They used to have the military sports and all. Matron saw us once with - they used to come and meet us see from 
work. She saw us once, she was coming up the hill, the next day she came in and told us she says -Be careful of these men - they come and go!" We laughed oh she was a dear old matron and she wasn't very tall. She was ever so sweet. And there was one room 
t
hat was never used much there and sometimes we used to clean it out and sometimes we didn't. Do you know she could tell by the smell of that place whether it had been cleaned out? We used to leave it on purpose sometimes to see. Of course I never done any
 scrubbing, the other two did it there used to be }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2690719\charrsid3892558 an old lady there that did the }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4231\charrsid3892558 
dirty washing, that's when they messed the beds and all. Some of them can't help it. Oh we had one old lady there, she was quite normal like in her, nothing to be afraid of, sh
e used to do the ironing, she used to shout and carry on, I don't know who it was she used to be talking to, but it was always somebody downstairs. And she used to wet nearly all day long, terrible. You know most of them were private patients, see. And so
me of them, the curtains used to hang down and they used to sit and pick all this round the bottom. Yes all private they were. There was a good many of them.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6443588 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4231\charrsid3892558 What actually were you doing?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7219173 CW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4231\charrsid3892558 That was where I was laundress.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6443588 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4231\charrsid3892558 Oh you were head laundress?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7219173 CW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4231\charrsid3892558 Yes. It was a good job. See.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6443588 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4231\charrsid3892558 How many years were you there altogether?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7219173 CW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4231\charrsid3892558 
Oh I don't know how many years. I was there a long time, I liked that job. See and when Mum used to come down she used to see the Matron, I used to ask for a bi
t of time off, and she used to know what I wanted it for, well of course you could understand her, we used to there it was a bit of but you could understand because we were only girls, of course the two sisters down there, they lived there, so did the old
 lady. See. They were proper, no none of us lived in. They had their home down there, they had no mother but they'd got a father. And he had been in the Army. He was an old soldier.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6443588 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4231\charrsid3892558 So the matron wondered what was happening when you asked for time off?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7219173 CW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4231\charrsid3892558 
Yes, she used to ask me what I wanted it for and where did I go? And I used to tell her "Mother is coming down". Of course one day she was coming down she said she wanted to see Mother. Thought to myself "What does she want to see her for?" Well of
 course they used to tell ta}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2690719\charrsid3892558 l}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4231\charrsid3892558 es to her in these days, you couldn't do much oh yes. {\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname place}}Lot
{\*\xmlclose} of old tell tales about.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6443588 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4231\charrsid3892558 What were the people like where you had rooms?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7219173 CW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4231\charrsid3892558 Oh she was very nice. I felt sorry for her. She kept having children, poor begg}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2690719\charrsid3892558 
a}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4231\charrsid3892558 r. And
 they both of them - I think she met him in an institution. They had both been in institutions. He was like a nurse, yes, I didn't care a lot for him though. She kept on having them. I said to her "I should shut the door to him, I know"
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6443588 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4231\charrsid3892558 Yes, it must be terrible.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7219173 CW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4231\charrsid3892558 
Well I think so, it is a miserable life I think for a woman to keep on having them. I wouldn't have them. Only had two, that was enough for me.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6443588 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4231\charrsid3892558 What happened after you left {\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname City}}{\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname place}}Canterbury{\*\xmlclose}{\*\xmlclose}
 then?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7219173 CW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4231\charrsid3892558 Came home. I had to. Because of the w
ar. It was terrible down there, you could hear the blooming guns! And they were always being called out in the night, Sergeants used to come in and call and the bugle would go and they used to sleep round in a circle. Yes, on the floor. Poor little devils
.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6443588 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4231\charrsid3892558 So you came home and helped your mother again did you?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7219173 CW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4231\charrsid3892558 
Of course I had to, where could you go? The blessed war. It was awful. Then we had another one! Blooming Germans upset the whole world. Haven't they? (And all these blessed blacks here - d
o you like the Blacks? And they are getting - I like the Cypriots. We've got a little shop round the corner, and she's just carrying her second baby, oh and they are nice. They call her Tina and he is Chris. They are, they are ever so nice, I go round the
re for me milk. Ever so nice. But I never fancy buying the food}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2690719\charrsid3892558  }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4231\charrsid3892558 
in there! You should see the melons they have there, very nice they are.)
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6443588 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4231\charrsid3892558 How did you meet your husband?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7219173 CW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4231\charrsid3892558 In the institution.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6443588 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4231\charrsid3892558 How old were you then?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7219173 CW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2690719\charrsid3892558 Well about 30}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4231\charrsid3892558  then.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6443588 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4231\charrsid3892558 Had you known him a long time?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7219173 CW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4231\charrsid3892558 Only about }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2690719\charrsid3892558 2}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4231\charrsid3892558  years.

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6443588 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4231\charrsid3892558 This was after the war then was it?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7219173 CW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4231\charrsid3892558 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6443588 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4231\charrsid3892558 so you went back there?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7219173 CW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4231\charrsid3892558 No, I didn't go back there. I went to another institution. Yes, I like}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2690719\charrsid3892558 
 it. I used to be up at Kings}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4231\charrsid3892558 . Up there 
for a long time. I saw the Supervisor there the other day, she recognized me. I wondered if she would. Tall woman. Now, they are allowed to go have a holiday at Christmas time. That is a new thing. Didn't used to have that. She's already had one week}{
\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2690719\charrsid3892558 \rquote }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4231\charrsid3892558 s holiday. She went to {\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname place}}{\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname City}}Cornwall{\*\xmlclose}
{\*\xmlclose}. She had nice weather when she was away and I think she had just come home. She told me "I'm having another one at Christmas" I look at her "Yes, she said. It is a new thing isn't it. We have one for Christmas. We'd never done that before."

\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6443588 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4231\charrsid3892558 What holidays had you when you started?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7219173 CW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4231\charrsid3892558 
